body:
Hi,

I would like to know if it's possible to distinct the query at widget level or to undistinct at widget level ?

Use case :
My index represents all the offers of my shop. Unfortunatly, i have to use this index to build my search UI for listing products.
my datas are structured like this :
```
[
  {
    merchant: {
        id : 1,
        name: "Merchant 1"
     },
    product: {
        id: 1,
        name: "Product 1",
        category: "Category 1"
    },
    price: 50
  },
  {
    merchant: {
        id : 2,
        name: "Merchant 2"
     },
    product: {
        id: 1,
        name: "Product 1",
        category: "Category 1"
    },
    price: 50
   },
  {
    merchant: {
        id : 1,
        name: "Merchant 1"
     },
    product: {
        id: 2,
        name: "Product 2",
        category: "Category 1"
    },
    price: 100
   },
  {
    merchant: {
        id : 2,
        name: "Merchant 2"
     },
    product: {
        id: 2,
        name: "Product 2",
        category: "Category 1"
    },
    price: 100
   },
]
```

I have to use the distinct = 1 to show only the two products. I have to use also facetAfterDistinct = true otherwise the count is not good for the refinement category.

The actual result is :

nb Hits = 2 (Product 1 and Product 2)

Categories List :
- Categorie 1 (2) <--- If facetAfterDistinct = false the count will be 4 (wrong because we want 2 like the hits)

Merchant List :
- Merchant 1 (2)  <--- there is no "Merchant 2" because of facetAfterDistinct=true, if we use facetAfterDistinct=false, there is the two merchants.  

The distinct parameter keep the first data of all products but we would like to have all merchants available for refinement...

We would like this result : 

nb Hits = 2 (Product 1 and Product 2)

Categories List :
- Categorie 1 (2) 

Merchant List :
- Merchant 1 (2)  
- Merchant 2 (2)


So is it possible to bypass the distinct at widget level ? or facetAfterDistinct ?

Maybe you have a better idea ?

Thanks
